<TITLE> Bangladesh get off to a flying start in AHF Cup </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 14 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh hockey team made a flying start in the 3rd AHF Cup with a convincing 6-1 win over Brunei Darussalam in their tournament opener in Singapore Saturday. Bangladesh led the first half 2-1 and later added four goals to make a winning start in the meet. Musa Mia put Bangladesh ahead in the 16th minute from a field goal while Rasel Mahmud Jimmy doubled the lead in the 22nd minute also from a field goal. Six minutes later, Brunei pulled one goal back with Akim Shalizan reducing the margin from a field goal to end the first half 2-1. After the breather, Bangladesh dominated over the minnows and Jimmy widened the margin converting a penalty corner three minutes into the second half. Medio Jahidul Islam Rajon made it 5-1 scoring two field goals in the span of two minutes while Jimmy sealed the match scoring his third and team's sixth goal in the 59th minute. Bangladesh face Chinese Taipei Sunday in their second encounter. 
